## Running Tests

```bash
# Full automated journey (4 spec files, ~50s)
npm run test:journey

# Individual suites
npm run test:smoke          # Window smoke tests
npm run test:api            # API integration tests
npx playwright test test/e2e/spaces-flow.spec.js
npx playwright test test/e2e/settings-flow.spec.js

# All E2E tests
npm run test:e2e
```

## How to Use These Plans

1. Open the area plan for the feature you are testing
2. Follow the Prerequisites section to set up
3. Work through the checklist top-to-bottom
4. Mark items `[x]` as you complete them
5. For `[A]` items, run the linked spec file or API command
6. For `[M]` items, perform the action manually and verify
7. For `[P]` items, run the automated part, then visually verify
8. Log any failures as issues with the area name as prefix

